column1: since mike passed i’ve received several pms or texts about a message from mike and i believe every single one of them! .
people aren’t going to just send random messages to someone who just lost their husband.  as a matter of fact most people feel more embarrassed to reach out
column2: but something inside them compels them to cast their feelings aside and just relay the message. .

column1: each time it’s been valuable in my healing and so grateful for the messages that comes from “behind the sunset”. .
so that’s why when i got a message from my friend jennifer

column1: she said mike came to her during the day and spoke to her in just a few sentences. .

column2: from india’s one daughter to another.

column1: hey nirbhaya!! it’s been six years since you’ve gone and a lot has changed.

column2: and a lot to comment on. a lot to give speeches on. a lot of obscene stuff to finally come out. a lot of truths to be falsified.

column1: as another dawn is set to rise.
you have taught me how to be fearless.
you gave me the courage to voice
to speak up and try to shine.
right from new chilli sprays to authentic destructive wear
from female cab drivers to women-centric films
from bold women coming out and #metoo movements
we have learnt from you how to be true twenty-one year olds.
my dad tries to talk about rape over the dinner table and my mom about pride.
my friends over politics and my seniors about visions.

column3: it has been six years now.

column1: yet we still worship and slaughter alarming rates of females still
and male assault has also become popular more so
yet your generation is working in worldly ways
to provide and protect generation next from what you are
i hope they fear what your spirit will become
i hope they await what fearlessness brings
i hope they bring about what you left lingering.

column2: pero callamos porque crecimos en una sociedad machista que te acostumbro asi porque sino era una vergüenza. en mi caso sufri violencia en diferentes momentos de mi vida: en la primaria y secundaria tuve que soportar la burla de mis compañeros varones por mi cuerpo porque me desarrolle antes de tiempo y por eso ya era motivo de burla; en la universidad soporte acoso por parte de profesores que intentaban levantarme o que en plena clase se burlaban de mis partes del cuerpo y me bancaba ver como todos mis compañeros se reían y ninguno me defendía
column3: pero claro yo me enojaba y era la ortiva
column4: llegue a denunciar a un profesor por acoso y por tratarme de puta delante de todos mis compañeros
column5: fui con un abogado y aún así el siguió en su puesto y me desaprobaba en la materia claro el tenia el poder. sufrí con ex novios que de puta no me bajaban cuando se enojaban
column6: también sufrí violencia física de parte de uno de ellos y no sali de mi casa por una semana porque me daba vergüenza que alguien viera mi ojo morado. y a pesar de todo esto que vivi

column1: the european court of human rights (ecthr) ruled thursday that an austrian woman's criminal conviction and fine for her statements accusing the prophet muhammad of pedophilia did not breach her right to free speech.⁣
the decision by a seven-judge panel came as an austrian national identified as e.s. by the court
column2: had held seminars on islam in 2008 and 2009 for the right-wing freedom party (fpo) where she discussed the prophet's marriage to his wife aisha
column4: and implied that he was a pedophile.⁣

column1: an austrian court convicted her of disparaging religious doctrines in 2011 and fined her 480 euros (548 dollars)
column2: a judgment that was upheld on two appeals.⁣

column1: stating that the court had found that ""the applicant's statements had been likely to arouse justified indignation in muslims"" and ""amounted to a generalization without factual basis""
column2: the strasbourg-based ecthr said that the woman's comments could not be covered by the freedom of expression.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

column1: 110166;instagram;2018-12-15 19:29:26;TRUE;;"do you know the difference between fear and eagerness? or excitement versus apprehension or anxiety?
fear: an unpleasant feeling triggered by the perception of danger.
apprehension: fear that something bad will happen.
excitement: a feeling of great enthusiasm or eagerness.

column3: moved by a strong and urgent desire or interest.

column1: oftentimes when we feel a strong emotion like fear or anxiety
column2: we allow that emotion to rule what we do and how we act
column3: or we even allow it to speak louder than our intuition

column1: it’s not really our fault. in fact
column2: we are programmed to run away from intense or “life-threatening” situations. our fight or flight kicks in
column3: which can be good if we are being attacked by a bear but can suck if we have the desire to do something exciting or different than what we’ve known.

column1: if you aren’t being attacked by a bear
column2: take a step back when you feel these emotions.

column1: how many times have you turned away
column4: or not taken that leap because you thought fear was telling you not to?

column1: what if you are misinterpreting fear for excitement? maybe if it’s scary
column2: it means it’s right! those butterflies in your stomach could be your soul telling you that you are doing it right! excitement and apprehension can be the same thing! you feel them both deep in your gut. trust what your body is telling you and go for it. what happens when we sit and think about how we react to certain emotions

column1: these emotions are visitors sent to help us on this journey
column2: but do we sit and listen or do we let them rule!?

column1: 110319;instagram;2018-12-16 15:48:29;FALSE;"this is a very important story to share and i hope you will take time to read the entire article. when this happened to me back in oct of last year
column2: i was made to believe it was an isolated incident and that the resort would handle everything and when i was distraught and upset got talked into signing a nda. it was until i saw that it had happened to another person at the same companies resort the night before her wedding that it made me sick to my stomach to find out this was happening to others. and that was just scratching the surface.

column1: i know these types of things happen elsewhere but it is about how tragic it is this company tries to cover up the crimes occurring and how they feel buying your silence is ok. they have even lied about what happened to me which i will further explain after the interview airs tomorrow morning on @goodmorningamerica

i will not ever be returning to any property owned by @sandalsresorts as they are morally and ethically corrupt in their handlings of sexual assaults that occur to their vactioners. i actually had hope that they would come out and admit there was a problem and that they knew they had to do better to ensure the safety of those who visit their properties but that wasn’t the case at al as you will see on the interview. there are so many other properties you can choose from when choosing your vacation spot. think twice before booking at a @sandalsresorts property as they do not have your best interest at heart. i am also sharing the article link in my bio above. please
column2: i ask that you share this article with others because we need to let as many people know. large corporations have to do better and can’t hide behind money to make these issue go away.

column1: it was a vacation ruined for me that i will never get back and i won’t be the same because of what happened to me but i do believe the good that can come of this is creating awareness about international travel as a whole and help others just be aware. #metoo #sandlasresort #sexualassault #sandalsochibeachresort #sandalsscandal #coverup #instagram

column1: this is the second survivor story submitted to #thesurvivortreeproject. transcribing this anonymous young woman’s story truly took me on a journey... she detailed five different encounters at the hands of five different men
column2: and not once was there a hint of anger or rage or vengeance coloring her story- only a need for someone to listen to her voice and believe her. she finished her essay with a powerful plea: two words “hear me.” i do hear you
column3: survivor. i believe you. you are so many things: kind
column9: empathetic... and so much more. this community is going to change the world. what happened to you is not the way things are
column10: but the way things were. the way things will be is up to us; and let me tell you- we’ve got this. together. that

column1: i had the opportunity to exchange a few messages with this woman
column2: and her heart is so big. we discussed the concept and importance of grief in all of its stages (including healthy anger)
column3: as well as the ideas of catharsis and closure. then she expressed concern for me and my wellbeing as it might be affected by internalizing all of these stories. i was honest with her and told her that i was worried about the effect it might have on my anxiety and cptsd
column4: but then she gave me a wonderful gift that i will hold so dear through this process of creating the survivor tree: she told me that with each story i transcribe i don’t have to feel heartbroken- because through this work
column5: survivors are healing. the power over these stories is evolving. and i have kept that with me which each story i’ve transcribed after that. i can never thank you enough for that

column1: 110330;instagram;2018-12-16 15:57:28;FALSE;"this spoke to me so much today. in a world that either tried to silence your voice
column2: or tell you what you “should” be doing

column1: i’ve been doing a lot of introspective work lately during development of my next program
column2: and one of the key lessons in the earlier weeks is peeling back the pages of your story that someone else wrote for you.  at what point in life did someone tell you that it’s not ok to want more? who told you that you would fail if you didn’t stay in that corporate america job? who told you that you would fail if you invest your savings into something you’ve always dreamed of but is scary as hell?  who told you that in order to be respected by professional men in the sales world that you have to be quiet
column4: and one step behind them?  who told you that money is just not for you
column5: or that it’s selfish to want more? and who told you that hardship and sickness in life is your lot in life?

column1: this section of learning is what often brings forth super raw emotions for my clients.  they must face the story that someone else wrote for them - and that they have allowed to be written for so many years.  however
column3: they are then given tools to take back the pen and write their next chapter. .

column1: if you’ve given power to someone else in life with your story
column2: i challenge you to recognize that today. you are a deserving being and no one else gets to write your story for you.

column1: went in to this just trying not to bomb out really. no expectations. weights felt a lot heavier than usual in the warm-up room
column2: so i lowered my opener to 518/235 from 530/240. third attempt wasn’t a pr
column3: but it was deeper and moved faster compared to last meet. re-tweaked my back here.

column2: but concerned. i tweaked my pec the week i hit 405 in the gym
column3: so i kept psyching myself out that i would tear it in the meet. looking back at the video

column2: but it was too late to lower my opener. it moved a lot slower than i would’ve liked. i felt the same pop in my back the time i hurt it in the gym
column3: so i was going to pass on my second attempt. but @thelifeofpauler convinced me otherwise

column1: i decided to pull without a belt because it feels comfortable and i can brace better. for my third attempt
column2: i went with 672/305 but a little hairless gorilla that goes by @lequadzilla said 694/315. i met him half way and chose 683/310. that turned out well.

column2: god will help you move it. just trust him. it’s easy to say that

column2: not ours. once we learn and accept that
column3: delays become much easier to accept.

column1: 110382;instagram;2018-12-16 15:19:57;FALSE;"i was recently in a professional development training and the trainer used this example.....

a little girl announced to her teacher that her daddy ate her cookie last night. the teacher barely acknowledged it and moved on with the class. it was later discovered that the child was being sexually abused and she had been taught to call her vagina her ""cookie"". now do you see why it's so important to teach your children the anatomically correct names for their body parts? in this scenario
column2: if she had been taught to use the proper terms for body parts

＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。

column1: i want to talk about something non vegan related but actually something that i think affects every single woman and vulnerable person on earth.... i’m afraid to walk anywhere or leave the house after dark.
with winter darkness sweeping over the u.k. by 4pm i’m swamped with this overwhelming feeling of dread
i had to walk to and from a friends house last night to take care of her doggo
column2: even without realising i’d dressed in the most androgynous clothes i could find so i’d look more like a male in my outdoor clothes
column3: i held my umbrella pointing outwards ready as a deterrent
column5: double checking every single man who walked past me
column6: analysing every man to see if he’s a threat
column7: i’m too scared to walk past any parks
column9: anywhere with trees or alleys is a no go
column13: i can’t even walk a few miles without worrying i’m going to be assaulted.

column1: a man hovering around a local wooded area last night made my heart pound in my chest
column2: do i risk walking past him? should i cross the road? i have gloves on can i reach my phone? i have lots of layers on and can’t bend my arms well can i defend myself if he attacks me? can i run? can i scream loud enough and would anyone hear me? my thoughts flash to my partner and daughter
column3: what if this is it for me? as a woman i genuinely fear for my life
column4: a woman had been raped only last week down this exact road
column5: it’s only 8:45pm but it doesn’t matter
column6: people are assaulted in broad daylight.

column1: not every man is a rapist
column2: not every man walking at night is a rapist
column3: not every man simply waiting for a lift from work or walking their dog is a rapist
column4: but as a woman walking in the dark
column5: it sure feels like every one is.

column1: from the moment we’re old enough we’re taught to prepare for being raped and assaulted
column5: it’s ingrained in us and something that’s only just dawned on me fully
column6: men are scared of being falsely accused
column7: women are scared to even leave our homes.

column2: please feel free to message me ❤️ #metoo #metoomovement";;en;#metoo

column1: 110463;instagram;2018-12-16 13:36:34;FALSE;"quick safety tip! leaning against a wall is always a great tactic when you want to reduce your blind spots and eliminate the possibility of someone getting behind you and catching you off guard.
1️⃣ leaning against a wall while waiting for the subway
2️⃣ choosing a seat at a restaurant with your back against a wall (or even better
3️⃣ finding a place at a bar where you can lean against a wall/surface .
important note❗️implementing violence prevention tactics/safety tips should not lead to a constant state of paranoia ❌
column2: rather a state of situational awareness that allows you to be alert and still enjoy the moments we are all fighting so hard to create 🤗.

;jag ser tillbaka till då jag var 8 år och minns att jag flera gånger både tänkte och sa högt : “ jag önskar jag var en kille. ” det handlade inte om det anatomiska eller biologiska , att jag ville bli penisbärare . nej , jag ville bara tillåtas vara lika bitsk , tala högt och känna mig trygg de intressen jag utvecklade vid ung ålder . även så ung ålder visste jag att något inte stämde , men först nu som vuxen kan jag sätta fingret på vad det var . hemma , - även fast mina föräldrar inte alltid förstod - kunde jag utöva mina intressen . men ute skolan , där jag skulle växa och lära , blev jag hela tiden placerad med de andra flickorna för att “ vara flicka ” , inte leka smutsen , inte säga fula saker , acceptera när killarna mobbade , slog och tog på en för att “ det är så killar är , de gillar dig. ” jag minns att när jag fick frågan “ vilken är din favorit prinsessa ? ” svarade jag alltid askungen , endast för att hon hade blå klänning och min favoritfärg är blå , hade aldrig sett filmen och var inte intresserad . jag gillade 'lejonkungen , spirit , och björnbröder ' , därför att de var djur , helt befriade från kraven att ingå en heteronormativ köns norm . varje gång de sprang eller vrålade ville jag göra detsamma . men det kunde jag inte , för att jag var människa , eller mer exakt : för att jag var flicka . jämställdhetsmyndigheten behövs , för att se till att barn inte ska behöva bli satta små fack av vuxna som inte vet bättre . så nu vrålar jag . för mitt 8 åriga själv som nu vuxen ålder vet att hon inte “ ville bli kille ” , hon ville bara inte placeras pga sitt kön ett förbestämt fack . jämställdhetsmyndigheten behövs , så att framtiden ingen ska behöva känna sig så förvirrad och så instängd som jag kände mig som barn . idag går jag ut för att protestera mot nedläggning och nedskärningar för vår framtid . ämställdhetsmyndigheten udget2019 eminist emonstration ;[('jag'

column1: 110501;instagram;2018-12-16 12:56:47;FALSE;jag vill avsluta mina två veckor som curator of höj rösten med en fan post. möt mina idoler! jag tänker att det är slutet på året och alla listor på människor att hålla koll på kommer att komma i olika former. men de här change makerserna kanske inte syns på listorna än. inte för att de inte hör hemma där utan för att vi har jobbat stenhårt med utbildningen och inte med media. de skriver debattartiklar
column4: är med i racet om posten som partisekreterare. de har tagit sig in i kommunfullmäktrige och nämnder. är experter vid samtyckeslagstiftningen
column5: är viktiga röster i rörelsen för #metoo och mansnormer. grundare till streetgäris och järvapolitilervecka. de är prisbelönta för sitt klimatarbete och håller key note speeches i bryssel och är sommarpratare i p1. de vaktar människors lika värde
column8: en begåvad och hållbar relation mellan stad och landsbygd. de brinner för hur våra gemensamma rum designas
column9: de vaktar ett värdigt mottagande när barn och familjer kommer ensamma över havet för att vi ska kunna vara den humanitära stormakt vi en gång var. de värnar den fria konsten och kulturella uttrycken för alla. de stöttar medborgare med intellektuell funktionsvariation i sitt deltagande i demokratiska processer. de transformerar utbildningssystemet så att nära generation lär för livet. de kämpar för att alla ska få älska vem dem vill. de vitaliserar demokratiska processer och gör världen lite brätte för oss alla att leva i. de är begåvade

column1: 110543;instagram;2018-12-16 09:32:21;FALSE;"one of my favourite responses to a brief we received last year was based on the many years of women marching for equality and the question: how far have women really come? eg with stats like “just 24 female ceos lead the companies on the 2018 fortune 500”
column2: and the #metoo movement highlighting a much needed rise up against sexism and inappropriate behaviour - it’s hard not to think that shift still needs to grow wider. it’s not about bashing men
column3: and saying all men in senior positions are bad
column4: it’s about saying there are still some abuses in power that need resolving. this year
column5: i’ve been reminded in the power of #sisterhood
column6: that after some bad experiences of powerful but unsupportive women
column7: that kindness and sisterhood is what drives me. through conferences/ talks/ meet-ups and being a mentor i was reminded in the power of women supporting other women
column8: and how wonderfully empowering that can feel.

column1: 110545;instagram;2018-12-16 10:12:56;FALSE;"मासिक धर्म के दिनों में कमजोर वर्ग की महिलाओं के बीच सैनेटरी नैपकिन की अनुपलब्धता कई कारणों से सरकार और विभिन्न सामाजिक संगठनों के लिए एक गंभीर चुनौती बनी हुई है। इस चुनौती से निपटने के लिए ngo जीवन अर्थ फाउंडेशन ने अपना कदम कई साल पहले ही बढ़ा दिया था।

हाल ही में फाउंडेशन द्वारा विभिन्न जगहों पर सैनिटरी नैपकिन बांटे गए। अलग अलग अवसरों पर ngo ये मुहीम शुरू करता है जिसमे किसी एक पिछड़े गांव या इलाके में जाके सैनिटरी पैड्स के पैकेट्स दान करता है। ngo ने 1000 पैकेट्स भी दान में दिए।
आगे बढ़ने की ओढ़ में अक्सर हम लोग यह भूल जाते हैं कि अगर हम अपने साथ अपने साथियों को न बढ़ा सके
column2: तो वह विकास नहीं होता। निश्चित तौर पर जिस तरह ngo निस्वार्थ भाव से इन कार्यों में आगे बढ़ रहा है
column3: उसी तरह हमें भी इनसे सीख लेनी चाहिए।

column2: women from lower classes find it difficult to arrange sanitary napkins because of various societal forces and governmental irregularities. looking at these issues
column3: ngo jeevan arth foundation has take the first step to provide this basic right to these women.

column2: ngo jeevan arth foundation distributed sanitary napkin packets at different places. in a campaign organized by the foundation
column3: ngo has been doing this for several years now. ngo jeevan arth foundation has also distributed 1000 sanitary napkin packets at one such event.

amor desamor vive constantemente pasando por un millón de desengaños . es cieo que tod tenemos una inspiración , un clic que nos hace tener la necesidad de escribir comunicar , con la palabra , con la música con las imágenes . mi motivación fue el movimiento mi mensaje es para todas las víctimas , para todos los agresores reales potenciales ( patada viual en los huevos para ellos ) . es gritar al mundo que las víctimas vamos dejar de sentirnos como tal . que con ayuda de familia , amig pareja también con ayuda profesional ( psicólogos , médicos , terapeutas , medicación cuando toca ) se sale time's up and the body representing hollywood producers swiftly announced that they will spend their share of the funds on programs to increase diversity in the entertainment industry

column1: people who have a mental health challenge do not have a life sentence to living a miserable life.  as someone living with ptsd it is part of my mission in life to help break the negative stigma that is attached to mental health.  know that just because you have been diagnosed with a mental health disorder that it is just that - a diagnosis.  it's not a dealth sentence and it is nothing to be ashamed of.  there is help out there in your area.
always  remember you are not alone and you can overcome anything you set your mind out to do because you are forever fat.  a true fighter
my purpose has become my passion and i am living my best life.  the fact that i get to help people with similar stories to mine along the way is a true blessing.
follow @foreverfatfridays for encouraging ways to learn how to overcome adversity.

column1: the victoria’s secret fashion show is dead
the annual victoria’s secret fashion show aired on december 2 garnered its lowest ratings ever.  does the world come to an end? i regard this as a very important
column2: progressive development. 1- people are more conscious about the standards of beauty imposed by the media and do not want to be the object anymore. 2- the idea of presenting women as a commodity is no longer attractive. 3- after #metoo movements and so on
column3: i think it is no longer fun to see standardized women on stage to entertain people.

「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。

column1: people like songs because of the stories they tell.  i like songs because of the stories behind them...the ones you don’t always hear about.  behind every song there’s a story in itself...sometimes a story of pain
column5: some type of journey.  i find the stories behind the songs fascinating.  like life these stories are never linear...they’re like our thoughts...super scattered
column7: sometimes scary...but all of them very real.  these are the stories we rarely get to hear.  i like capturing these feelings in my songwriting cuz i feel like people can relate to this. .

column1: but maybe even the most scattered thoughts and ideas that we often think are not wrong
column3: or random at all.  maybe it’s all a collection of tiny pieces and parts of us that’s makes us who we are.  these are the stories behind our lives that makes us us.  that’s the kind of songwriting i like to do.  and i’m not sure if that makes me a good songwriter or even if it makes for a good song but i know it makes for a real one.  and i know as people we are often concerned about the story our lives tell...but maybe we should be concerned about the stories behind them...the ones we rarely get to hear.  because those stories are worth telling

column1: 110756;instagram;2018-12-16 04:17:47;FALSE;"healing update number one thousand six hundred and seventy-two... 😉
lately i‘ve gotten so much better so quickly that i don’t think nearly as much about the specifics of what my alleged rapist put me through anymore.
it’s like i can breathe again and i’m so happy to be here.

column2: i’ve been forced to remember a little bit when i get ready every morning.

column1: one of the ways i allege i have been abused was being “project managed” to lose weight. it was dictated how many calories i ate and what exercise i did.
each day had a limit of seven hundred calories and at least two hours of exercise. i had to show my loss each week.
but starvation hits your body hard. i’d had physical health issues in recent years
column3: so very quickly my hair started falling out.

column1: it wreaked havoc on my entire body
column2: to be honest. i got a painful eye ulcer on the surface of my cornea from being hit. i get migraines now
column3: which started after being choked. my dentist would ask if i’d suffered a bereavement because she could see an interruption in the production of enamel on my teeth.

column2: i have been able to heal most of those symptoms. but the cycle of the hair follicle means it takes a lot of time to grow back. i hated being reminded of this whenever i looked in the mirror.

column1: so when loved ones offered to get me hair extensions for my birthday
column2: i couldn’t help but greedily take the gift.

column1: and i’m so glad i did.

column2: i am slayinggg 💃🏼 there’s so many things that i’ll never get back but having my glam returned to me is precious.

column1: thanks as always for letting me overshare. i’m so lucky to have a deeply kind community of people who let me process this out loud.

column1: 110772;instagram;2018-12-16 02:49:03;FALSE;"this is the second survivor story submitted to #thesurvivortreeproject. transcribing this anonymous young woman’s story truly took me on a journey... she detailed five different encounters at the hands of five different men
column2: and not once was there a hint of anger or rage or vengeance coloring her story- only a need for someone to listen to her voice and believe her. she finished her essay with a powerful plea: two words “hear me.” i do hear you
column3: survivor. i believe you. you are so many things: kind
column9: empathetic... and so much more. this community is going to change the world. what happened to you is not the way things are
column10: but the way things were. the way things will be is up to us; and let me tell you- we’ve got this. together. that

column1: i had the opportunity to exchange a few messages with this woman
column2: and her heart is so big. we discussed the concept and importance of grief in all of its stages (including healthy anger)
column3: as well as the ideas of catharsis and closure. then she expressed concern for me and my wellbeing as it might be affected by internalizing all of these stories. i was honest with her and told her that i was worried about the effect it might have on my anxiety and cptsd
column4: but then she gave me a wonderful gift that i will hold so dear through this process of creating the survivor tree: she told me that with each story i transcribe i don’t have to feel heartbroken- because through this work
column5: survivors are healing. the power over these stories is evolving. and i have kept that with me which each story i’ve transcribed after that. i can never thank you enough for that
column6: survivor. ✨🌱 click the link in my bio if others would like to contribute your story. #survivor #believesurvivors #believewomen #believeblackwomen #rapesurvivor #thesurvivortreeproject #metoo #timesup #endrapeculture #metoomovement";;en;#TheSurvivorTreeProject.

column1: for many years i thought that those uncomfortable situations that i have lived with the masculine gender had happened only to me and that i was guilty of it. but thanks to other women have spoken
column2: i  realized that i am not the only one.

column1: i am 25 years old and it is not easy for me to say my age after they have taught us by a lot of advertising slaps that an older woman becomes ‘less valuable’
column2: and that adult men become interesting over the years (and even reggaeton songs are dedicated “i like older men
column3: of those who are called gentlemen”). anyway.

column1: but today i comment my age with pride
column2: because in these two decades and five years
column3: i have grown as a woman and embraced my gender condition day by day. therefore
column4: now i can take a deep breath and narrate in the form of catharsis all those situations in which i have felt disadvantaged or confused. since in dialogues with other sisters i have found that most of us go through the same and we have been forced to shut up because if we complain we are ´hysterical´as we were diagnosed a few years ago whenever we rebelled
column5: and because every woman demands justice and fairness is accused of ‘feminazi’
column6: through social networks and in juvenile contexts (which should be
column8: the most open mind). this is the announcement of periodic publications that i will start to have on my blog
column10: because most of those people have apologized already and because we do not seek revenge
column11: only respect. i will do an exercise of love and conscience
column12: not hate. i have two brothers who remind me that we educate men and that in our hands is the opportunity to correct with benevolence and firmness behaviors that we are not forced to stand.

column3: for sharing this intimate space with me. welcome girls and boys! my blog: ephymeral.wordpress.com 🍬

column1: kelebihan cecair perangsang wanita blue wizard:
📍merangsang wanita untuk melakukan seks.membuat wanita ghairah dengan melampau.membuat wanita gatal pada bahagian kemaluan.buat wanita menjadi gila seks sehingga tidak boleh dikawal.
📍blue wizard tidak berwarna(warna seperti air mineral)
cara penggunaan blue wizard untuk ghairah seks wanita :
satu botol perangsang wanita blue wizard boleh digunakan untuk berkali-kali
column2: kerana isi lebih banyak dibandingkan dengan ubat perangsang cair wanita lainnya.cukup 5-10 titis blue wizard dimasukkan ke dalam minum apa saja
column3: kecuali susu dan air kelapa muda.lebih baik diminum dengan minuman yang bersoda
column6: coca-cola dll. ubat perangsang blue wizard juga dapat diminum tanpa campuran minuman lainnya. hanya dalam waktu 10-15 minit sahaja sudah berkesan.

📍blue wizard tidak berwarna(warna seperti air mineral)
cara penggunaan blue wizard untuk ghairah seks wanita :
satu botol perangsang wanita blue wizard boleh digunakan untuk berkali-kali
column2: kerana isi lebih banyak dibandingkan dengan ubat perangsang cair wanita lainnya.cukup 5-10 titis blue wizard dimasukkan ke dalam minum apa saja
column3: kecuali susu dan air kelapa muda.lebih baik diminum dengan minuman yang bersoda
column6: coca-cola dll. ubat perangsang blue wizard juga dapat diminum tanpa campuran minuman lainnya. hanya dalam waktu 10-15 minit sahaja sudah berkesan.

column1: 110984;instagram;2018-12-15 21:43:48;FALSE;"one moment your life is lived by a young child who's soul is innocent and full of dreams!!
flash forward to when that innocence was taken at the tender age of 5!! then again and again. noone is there to help and you now turn to a cold
column2: distrusting teenager. who blames every bad thing that's happened to her on the curl world. for years she spent time craving attention from the wrong people because of the abuse sustained in her life! she can't trust
column3: she can't live and she feels worthless. she doesn't take the time to love her self and understand that her feelings are normal.

column1: life hits her hard again and this time she wants to quit. just end it since noone cares about the agony shes been living for 20 years of her life.
that could have been the end of my story because that girl is me.
instead i used my voice and asked for help with the hopes it would work. i've heard from so many people that turning for help was the best decision of their life and i can see why.
i choose to continue my story and use my voice with the hope's i can help even just 1 person💓
